MemberSignature.Value: public: property int RES_ID { int get(); void set(int value); };
member this.RES_ID : int with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the ordinal identifier of a resource.

remarks.para: The default value is -1. As you create or add resources to the project, Microsoft Project automatically assigns the next number in the sequence of resources listed. This value becomes the RES_ID.
RES_ID is not a unique identifier for the resource. It changes whenever the order of resources changes. The persistent unique identifier is the property.

member this.RES_MATERIAL_LABEL : string with get, set

Docs.summary: Gets or sets the text that specifies the units for a material resource.

remarks.para: The default value is 2. This field applies only if the property is set to type . The Material Label field contains the unit of measurement you enter for supplies or other consumable items that are used to complete tasks in a project; for example, tons, boxes, or cubic yards. This label is then used in conjunction with the material resource's assignment units; for example, eight tons or 22 boxes.
